newsitem.title: USA: CBOT overnight Project A ag volume 1,227 contracts.
newsitem.headline: CBOT overnight Project A ag volume 1,227 contracts.

text.p: The Chicago Board of Trade Project A overnight agricultural trading volume totalled 1,227 contracts compared with 1,485 overnight Wednesday, according to the CBOT.
There were 109 wheat, 460 corn, 588 soybean, 41 soymeal, and 25 soyoil and four oat contracts traded. Fifteen corn calls and one soybean call was traded.
In overnight trading, wheat was 1-1/4 lower to 1/2 cent per bushel higher, corn was 1-1/4 cent to 1/2 cent lower and soybeans were two to 1-3/4 cents lower.
